  "__comment": [
    "Old-spelling -> modern-spelling mappings, applied by the SPELLING layer",
    "(normalizeSpelling). Both indexed text and search queries pass through",
    "this table, so a search for either form finds both. Keys are folded base",
    "forms (lower-case, accents stripped, ae/oe ligatures expanded, apostrophes",
    "removed, so \"tho'\" appears here as \"tho\"); values are the modern",
    "spelling, a real word. Map the base form only: the form layer below",
    "Porter-stems the result, so inflections (shews/shewn) are caught from a",
    "single \"shew\" -> \"show\" row. The existing inflected rows are redundant",
    "but harmless. Map an old spelling to its modern spelling, never to a stem."
  ],
